default1.4
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHorizon scanning is one of a number of tools that futures research
defaulters use which can be employed to test future policy and strategy
default. P
defaultractitioners do not normally use the term horizon scanning to describe all futures research techniques: it is one method in a wider toolkit used by futures research practitioners
default and is
default the
default act of gathering new insights that may point us towards affirming or discrediting existing trends and developments, as well as identifying new and emerging trends and developments which will impact on our lives in the future.
default The Jon Day Review appears to
default use the term to describe wider futures research methods. For the purposes of this submission, we will use the term ‘futures research’ to describe the
default full range of
default methods used by futures practitioners to analyse possible futures. 
defaultWhere the term ‘horizon 
defaultscanning
default’
default is used, 
defaultit describes the action set out above. 
