default1.5
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThere are a number of observable differences in undertaking futures research from other, perhaps more familiar research methods. We do not go into detail here, but suggest that should Committee me
defaultmbers so wish, they may find value in reading the review of futures research undertaken by Defra (2006), but which does not appear as part of the literature review undertaken as part of the Day Review. We consider that a good understanding of these differe
defaultnces is key in helping Ministers and senior officials to understand, develop and use the outputs of futures research. Additionally, it should be noted that a number of the recommendations made in the Day Review reflect those identified in the earlier Defra
default work. 
